      <h2>What I build</h2>
      <div class="fields">
        <article class="field dev">
          <h3>Web applications</h3>
          <p>Modern and fast, with an Angular frontend, built accessibility-minded (WCAG-oriented). Runs in the browser, nothing to install for the user.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="field dev">
          <h3>APIs &amp; backends</h3>
          <p>Cleanly structured with NestJS and PostgreSQL. The foundation your application runs on reliably and extensibly, no spaghetti that collapses at the first change request.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="field dev">
          <h3>Workflow &amp; approval systems</h3>
          <p>Requests, reviews, multi-stage approvals, with roles, server-enforced rules and a complete history. Exactly the kind of internal software no off-the-shelf product covers.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="field dev">
          <h3>Real-time &amp; operations included</h3>
          <p>Changes appear instantly, no reloading. And operations are part of the deal: Docker, HTTPS, on your server or hosted by me. I don't just hand over code, I hand over a running application.</p>
